<br>
Yes, this is Zatranik, a foolish-seeming Iksar that always changes characters on Firiona Vie, and has a new account now. How do you people do this? How do you stay with one character for so long? Teach me your methods, oh great ones! <br>
<br>
  As you can see by my account name, I'm a fan of Teir'Dal, and like to roleplay them, but still can't seem to stick with but one character. <br>
<br>
  If you teach me how you actually can stand staying as one character, or how you make your character so interesting to roleplay, you'll have a new roleplayer on FV, and a dood hater. As I've been MUCKing for a while, and love to roleplay, as well as being a self-proclaimed good roleplayer, I'd love to roleplay on FV. Even if I find it easier to roleplay on text-based systems, I'm doing it for you people too, as there aren't many roleplayers left!<br>
<br>
  Yes, so, please tell me how. I'm guessing one way would be to write up a history and stuff on your character, but you have to have some other ways too, right? Because even writing up a history and getting into roleplaying the character, I might get bored of the character. Thank yous.<br>
<br>
