<br>
Though, recently, the bug has been re-surfacing itself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :| --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/indifferent.gif ALT=":|"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I finally came to the painful realization that no matter how much I might want to or how hard I might try, I'll never be able to see the end-game stuff in person.  My real-life schedule and situation precludes it.  That being the case, the drive to keep one character to end-game is no longer there, and the urge to try other characters arises again.<br>
<br>
I've got an Iksar character and a Vah Shir character trying to claw their way to the surface ....<br>
<br>
My best advice to you, if you wish to keep to one specific character is similar to Caillou's ... find a series of goals for the character to work toward ... acheive one, and then go on to the other one ... acheive it, and then go on to the next, and so forth.  Nidge's specific goals were crafting ones. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://carim.home.mindspring.com/thenidge1.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
